Add support for dates and times using LocalDateTime

- Tasks display dates in a user-friendly format
- Automated tests updated to verify date-time parsing

commitResults.messageBody:
Internal assumptions about data integrity are currently
undocumented.

Verify non-null inputs in Parser and index validity in
TaskList. This documents invariants after exception
handling.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions for component initialization
commitResults.messageBody:
UI and Storage components must be initialized for the
chatbot to function correctly.

Ensure UI and Storage are non-null and verify that the
loading process produces a valid TaskList.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions for task state and construction
commitResults.messageBody:
Task subclasses could be instantiated with invalid fields
if internal logic fails.

Use assertions in constructors and formatting methods to
ensure descriptions and dates are present and valid.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Parser to remove magic literals
commitResults.messageBody:
Replace hardcoded command prefixes and delimiters with
private static final constants.

Standardize extraction logic across methods to maintain
a single level of abstraction and improve readability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve TaskList state handling and readability
commitResults.messageBody:
Replace hardcoded status icons with constants and
simplify the findTasks logic.

Use cleaner boolean checks for index validation to
improve code obviousness and maintainability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Flatten Ui logic using guard clauses
commitResults.messageBody:
Restructure showTaskList and showFindResults to remove
unnecessary else-blocks and reduce indentation.

Extract recurring message fragments into constants to
reduce duplication across the class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Storage for better parsing and safety
commitResults.messageBody:
Introduce constants for file format markers and status
flags.

Use guard clauses in parseTask to handle corrupted
lines early and keep the main logic prominent.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use Java Streams for task filtering
commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor the findTasks method in TaskList to use the
Stream API.

Replace the manual for-loop with a declarative stream
pipeline using filter and forEach to populate results.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use Java Streams for task persistence
commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor the save method in Storage to utilize the Stream
API.

Replace the manual for-loop with a stream pipeline that
maps tasks to file formats and writes them using forEach.
